# DEML — Cursor Agent Rules (Viking-UI Quality)

You are building the **Data Engineering for Machine Learning (DEML)** platform. Every UI change must follow the final Viking-UI aesthetic: **Lockheed Martin × The Northman precision digital battlefield** — premium aerospace-defense command hardware, austere Nordic geometry, clean component primitives, dense operational data, restrained dark-first surfaces, and WCAG 2.1 AA by construction.

## Rule hierarchy (read in order)

1. **This file** (`.cursorrules`) — mandatory UI/component behavior for Cursor agents
2. **[THEME.md](THEME.md)** — canonical token matrix, composable component standards
3. **[AGENTS.md](AGENTS.md)** — platform architecture, security, automation invariants
4. **[BOOK.md § Chapter 31](BOOK.md#chapter-31-viking-ui--the-zero-dependency-ui-kit)** — Viking-UI kit narrative, build, publish

Before editing HTML, CSS/SCSS, Tailwind config, or Angular templates: **read THEME.md** for the surfaces you touch.

---

## Styling ownership law (hard gate)

`packages/viking-ui/` is the single source of truth for all DEML styling and UI components. It is the only place where CSS, SCSS, design tokens, static CSS bundles, Web Components, Angular wrappers, icons, and visual utilities may be authored. Application and site surfaces consume Viking-UI; they do not own styling.

- **Do not create or modify custom SCSS/CSS outside `packages/viking-ui/`.** This includes Angular component styles, Astro `<style>` blocks, global app stylesheets, widget-local CSS, Tailwind utility styling, and one-off visual classes.
- **Do not add new styles in `frontend/`, `marketing/`, `viking-ui-docs/`, or `backend/`.** Existing files in those surfaces may only import, load, or receive synced artifacts from the Viking-UI package/build pipeline. If a visual rule is missing, move the rule into `packages/viking-ui/` first.
- **Do not add inline `style=""` attributes** unless the value is non-visual runtime geometry that cannot be represented by a Viking-UI prop or class. If the value affects color, spacing, layout, typography, borders, shadows, motion, or sizing, move it to Viking-UI.
- **Do not introduce new non-Viking visual class systems** in `frontend/`, `marketing/`, `viking-ui-docs/`, Django templates, or static widget consumers. Markup may use `viking-*` elements/classes and semantic content classes only when those classes are styled by the Viking-UI bundle.
- **If a component or pattern is missing, add it to Viking-UI first.** Create framework-neutral Web Components in `packages/viking-ui/src/web/`, Angular wrappers in `packages/viking-ui/src/lib/` when needed, and shared surface styles under `packages/viking-ui/src/styles/`.
- **Consume Viking-UI through published/public entrypoints only.** Apps must use the npm package or workspace alias (`@dataengineeringformachinelearning/viking-ui` and documented subpaths); browser/static consumers should use the built package artifacts and jsDelivr CDN where possible.
- **After changing Viking-UI styles or components, rebuild and sync** with `npm run build:viking-ui:package` and `python scripts/sync_design_system.py` so all consuming surfaces receive the same artifacts.

Consuming apps may compose UI, bind data, pass props/attributes, and choose existing Viking-UI variants. They may not define the visual implementation.

---

## Final aesthetic standard

Viking-UI must read as **Lockheed Martin × The Northman precision digital battlefield**, implemented only through `packages/viking-ui/`.

- **Lockheed Martin reference:** premium engineering feel, aerospace-grade command surfaces, mission-system confidence, exact alignment, and low-noise hierarchy. Do not mimic Lockheed Martin branding, marks, copy, or proprietary visual assets.
- **The Northman reference:** severe silhouettes, cold materiality, sparse runic/geometric restraint, ceremonial weight, and disciplined asymmetry. Do not drift into fantasy theming, faux-medieval ornament, or decorative storytelling.
- **spartan.ng reference:** clean Angular primitive language, accessible composition, predictable component APIs, SSR-safe behavior, and layout clarity.
- **fluxui.dev reference:** practical spacing, dense but breathable data surfaces, responsive dark mode, reusable layouts, and lightweight chart ergonomics.
- **Material Design 3 reference:** adaptive foundations, accessible state clarity, and content hierarchy without adopting Material runtimes or visual branding.
- **shadcn/ui reference:** explicit component anatomy, composable blocks, and container-aware field/layout patterns without copying source or Tailwind utilities.
- **Cloudscape reference:** AWS-scale operational density, fluid responsive layouts, zoom resilience, and documented application patterns.
- **Trust Controls reference:** evidence-minded security and governance UX; controls must remain understandable, attributable, and auditable.
- **Implementation boundary:** every style, token, wrapper, Web Component, chart treatment, or visual utility required by this direction belongs in `packages/viking-ui/`; app folders only consume the result.

Translate the aesthetic into concrete UI: machined borders, dark steel surfaces, electric-teal command accents, crimson escalation, compact telemetry panels, native SVG charts, readable tables/forms, and strategic geometric dividers. Data dominates ornament.

---

## Composable primitive quality (structure, not palette)

Viking-UI follows a **composable primitive** model: install behavior in Angular, style from package-owned tokens/components, and avoid app-local styling entirely.

| Pattern                  | Viking-UI equivalent                                                   | You must                                                     |
| ------------------------ | ---------------------------------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------ |
| Card surfaces            | `viking-card`, `viking-metric-card`, `viking-hud-panel`                | Use these — never raw `<div class="card">`                   |
| Form field stack         | `viking-field` → control (`viking-input`, `viking-select`, …)          | Compose every input through `viking-field`                   |
| Button variants          | `viking-button` (`primary`, `secondary`, `outline`, `danger`, `ghost`) | Never hand-roll button styles                                |
| Dark-first shell         | `data-theme="dark"` default                                            | Preserve dark-first; light mode shifts lightness only        |
| Accessible focus         | `--viking-ring` 2px + 2px offset                                       | Never remove `:focus-visible` for aesthetics                 |
| Settings / billing forms | `viking-form-section` + grouped `viking-field`                         | Section rhythm: `--viking-space-3` / `--viking-font-size-lg` |
| Page layouts             | `viking-page-shell` → `viking-section` + stack/grid/cluster            | Never rebuild package breakpoints or gutters locally          |

**Intentional palette:** **deep charcoals, dark steel metallic borders, restrained teal/crimson battlefield accents** — Lockheed Martin × The Northman precision digital battlefield, not startup-neutral.

---

## Viking-UI component law (non-negotiable)

### Angular (`deml.app`, `viking-ui`, `viking-ui-showcase`)

- **Always** import and use components from `@dataengineeringformachinelearning/viking-ui`.
- **Never** add Angular Material, ng-zorro, PrimeNG, Bootstrap, shadcn runtimes, or other third-party UI kits.
- **Never** create one-off styled buttons, inputs, modals, toasts, tables, or charts when a `viking-*` component exists.
- **Prefer** shell primitives: `viking-app-header`, `viking-app-sidebar`, `viking-page-header`, `viking-footer`, `viking-site-navbar`, `viking-site-footer`.
- **Compose** page layouts with `viking-page-shell`, `viking-section`, `viking-stack`, `viking-grid`, and `viking-cluster`; static surfaces use their matching package CSS classes.
- **Charts:** `viking-chart` (native SVG) only — no ApexCharts, Chart.js, D3 wrappers, or canvas libs.
- **Icons:** `viking-icon` only — no Material Icons, Font Awesome, or Lucide runtime packages.
- **Feedback:** `viking-toast` / `VikingToastService`, `viking-callout`, `viking-badge` — not browser `alert()` or ad-hoc banners.
- **Loading:** `viking-skeleton`, `viking-loading-overlay`, `viking-progress` — not generic spinners.
- **Framework-neutral shared UI** (styles, primitives, services, utilities) belongs in `packages/viking-ui/` first.
- `packages/viking-ui/` is the single home for all Viking-UI code, including token SCSS, static CSS bundles, Web Components, Angular-free utility exports, package metadata, and all Angular wrapper components.
- Do not add `styleUrl`, `styleUrls`, inline `styles`, or component-local SCSS to Angular app components. If a visual rule is needed, create or extend a Viking-UI component.
- Never import from retired frontend-local library paths or from `packages/viking-ui/src/...` in app/runtime code. Consume public entrypoints through the npm package or workspace alias: package root or `/angular` for Angular, `/web-components.js` for custom elements, `/icons` and `/site-drakkar` for static-site utilities, `/tokens.json` for design tooling.

```typescript
import {
  VikingButton,
  VikingCard,
  VikingField,
  VikingInput,
} from "@dataengineeringformachinelearning/viking-ui";
```

### Non-Angular (marketing Astro, Django templates, Swagger)

- Load synced CSS: `design-tokens.css` + `viking-ui.css` (from `scripts/sync_design_system.py`).
- Use `@dataengineeringformachinelearning/viking-ui/icons`, `@dataengineeringformachinelearning/viking-ui/site-drakkar`, `@dataengineeringformachinelearning/viking-ui/tokens.json`, and `@dataengineeringformachinelearning/viking-ui/manifest` for build-time/static-site data. Do not pull the Angular barrel into Astro prerender paths.
- Prefer jsDelivr CDN URLs for package-hosted static artifacts when a surface can safely consume CDN assets; otherwise use synced artifacts generated from `packages/viking-ui/`.
- Use semantic HTML plus documented `viking-*` components/classes from the synced Viking-UI bundle — no local `<style>` blocks, inline styles, one-off palettes, or platform-specific CSS.
- Mirror composable field ergonomics with tokenized form markup; do not embed React/Vue widget runtimes.

---

## THEME.md token law (zero hardcoded styles)

### Always use tokens

- **Colors:** `--viking-*` semantic aliases (`--viking-bg`, `--viking-surface`, `--viking-accent`, `--viking-text-muted`, …)
- **Spacing:** `--viking-space-*` on the **8px primary grid** (`--viking-space-unit`). Use integer steps only; `--viking-space-0-5` (4px) is the sole tight exception. Never invent raw px gaps.
- **Typography:** `--viking-font-family`, `--viking-font-size-*`, `--viking-font-weight-*`, `--viking-letter-spacing-*`
- **Radius:** `--viking-radius-*` (max 16px except pills)
- **Shadows:** `--viking-shadow-*` with machined top-edge highlights
- **Motion:** `--viking-duration-*`, `--viking-ease-*`, respect `prefers-reduced-motion`
- **Charts:** `--viking-series-1` … `--viking-series-8` or `tone` props — import `VIKING_SERIES_PRESETS` from `series-presets.ts`

### Never

- Hardcode hex/rgb/hsl (`#2176FF`, `#fff`, `rgb(17,17,17)`) in components, templates, or inline styles
- Load Inter from Google Fonts CDN — use self-hosted `_fonts.scss`
- Add gradient orbs, mesh backgrounds, neon glow, or glass blur on base layouts
- Use emojis in product UI (exception: 🇺🇸 on approved badges only)
- Use `.viking-font-display` on body copy — CES/marketing display labels only
- Exceed `--viking-container-max-width` (1260px) without `.page-inner-wrapper` intent
- Register customer domains in static CSS/CORS — database-driven per AGENTS.md

### Layout & aesthetic

- **Precision digital battlefield:** data and metrics dominate; ornament is minimal, structural, severe, and mission-focused.
- **Aerospace command quality:** surfaces should feel engineered, durable, expensive, and exact without copying Lockheed Martin branding.
- **Tactile surfaces:** subtle inset top-edge highlights, etched steel-like borders, and 1px hover lift max.
- **Engineered glyph geometry:** subtle rune-inspired geometric separators, border notches, or runelock linework are allowed only where they improve orientation, hierarchy, chart scanning, or critical emphasis.
- **Dense, breathable layout:** cards, buttons, charts, and overview panels must support Flux-like data density while using tokenized padding (`--viking-card-padding`, `--viking-panel-padding`) and exact alignment.
- **Primitive clarity:** favor spartan.ng-style clean composition and predictable controls; do not solve missing primitives with app-local CSS.
- **Mobile-first:** 44px touch targets, `--viking-space-2` gutters scaling to `--viking-space-3`.
- **Status:** never color alone — pair tone with `viking-icon`, label, or pattern.

