## Premium polish standards (locked)

Every surface must match the **marketing site polish bar** — use it as the visual benchmark before shipping UI.

**Visual benchmark:** [dataengineeringformachinelearning.com](https://dataengineeringformachinelearning.com/) (`marketing/src/pages/index.astro`, `marketing/src/styles/landing.scss`). Match its breathing room, section hierarchy, machined card surfaces, and restrained teal/crimson accents. If deml.app, backend, docs, or showcase feels flatter, less disciplined, or less legible than marketing, it is not done.

### Tokens only — spacing, color, wrappers

| Concern               | Required tokens / wrappers                                                                                                                                                                 | Never                                                                                           |
| --------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Spacing**           | `--viking-space-*`, `--viking-page-gutter` / `--viking-page-gutter-lg`, `--viking-page-stack-gap`, `--viking-page-section-gap`, `--viking-card-padding`, `--viking-panel-padding`          | Raw `px` gaps (`12px`, `20px`, `32px`) unless mapped 1:1 to a token                             |
| **Colors**            | `--viking-bg`, `--viking-surface`, `--viking-surface-recipe`, `--viking-text*`, `--viking-accent*`, `--viking-border` / `-subtle` / `-strong`, `--viking-success` / `-warning` / `-danger` | Hex, `rgb()`, `rgba()`, washed opacity stacks, legacy `--color-*` without `--viking-*` fallback |
| **Shell wrappers**    | `.page-inner-wrapper`, `viking-page-header`, `viking-card` (+ `viking-card-header` / `-footer` when structured), `viking-metric-card`, `viking-hud-panel`, `viking-form-section`           | Raw `<div class="card">`, hand-rolled panel shells, duplicate per-page card SCSS                |
| **Typography rhythm** | `--viking-font-size-*`, `--viking-line-height-*`, `--viking-letter-spacing-*`                                                                                                              | Ad-hoc `font-size: 1.1rem` without a token alias                                                |

### Minimum padding, margins, and max-widths

Enforce these floors on every page — no Spartan drift, no cramped KPI rows:

- **Page shell:** content lives in `.page-inner-wrapper` capped at `--viking-container-max-width` (1260px) with `--viking-page-gutter` (mobile) → `--viking-page-gutter-lg` (tablet+).
- **Section rhythm:** `--viking-page-section-gap` or `--viking-space-7` between major blocks; `--viking-space-3` between related subsections; use `.metrics-overview-header` + `.section-title-premium` patterns from `page-shell.scss`.
- **Card interiors:** minimum `--viking-card-padding` (`--viking-space-3`); compact metrics use `--viking-card-padding-compact` (`--viking-space-2`) — never below `--viking-space-2`.
- **Form stacks:** `viking-field` gaps and `viking-form-section` spacing at `--viking-space-2` minimum; billing/settings sections at `--viking-font-size-lg` titles with `--viking-space-3` vertical rhythm.
- **Readable copy width:** long prose/subtitles cap at `--viking-content-readable-max-width` (~48rem).
- **Touch targets:** interactive controls ≥ 44px height on mobile (`--viking-control-height` / `--viking-space-5` minimum).
- **Responsive grids:** use tokenized gaps (`--grid-gap`, `--viking-space-2`–`--viking-space-3`); collapse single-column on mobile before squeezing padding.

### Component wrapper law (Angular + static)

- Wrap every content block in a **`viking-*` primitive** before adding page-specific SCSS.
- Prefer **`--viking-surface-recipe`** + machined top hairline (`page-shell.scss` / `viking-card`) over flat `--viking-surface` fills.
- Charts, empty states, and loaders: `viking-chart-panel`, `viking-chart-empty-state`, `viking-skeleton` — not bespoke div shells.
- **DI in library components:** use constructor parameter injection — never field-level `inject()` in `@dataengineeringformachinelearning/viking-ui` (causes NG0203 in cross-package production bundles).

### Polish parity checklist (compare to marketing)

Before merge, confirm the touched surface matches marketing benchmark quality:

1. Generous vertical rhythm between hero → sections → cards (no edge-to-edge text blocks).
2. Metallic borders visible but restrained (`--viking-border`, not faint `rgba()` washes).
3. Accent color used sparingly — teal primary, crimson secondary; no neon or gradient orbs.
4. Hierarchy reads in one glance: page header → section title → metric/card → detail.
5. `node scripts/enforce-theme.js` and `node scripts/check_mobile_first.js` pass with zero violations.

